<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q11_v1" title="Q11_v1" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>Para convertir una distancia medida en millas a centímetros, se utiliza la siguiente regla: para obtener los centímetros, se multiplica la cantidad de millas por 160 934.</p>
    <div/>
    <p>Un sendero turístico tiene una longitud de 2,5 millas.</p>
    <p>Sabiendo que 
      <m:math>
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mn>1</m:mn>
          <m:mtext> kilómetro</m:mtext>
          <m:mo>=</m:mo>
          <m:mn>100&#160;000</m:mn>
          <m:mtext> centímetros</m:mtext>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>,
      ¿cuántos kilómetros mide el sendero?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="1">
      <qti-prompt>Seleccione una opción.</qti-prompt>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">40 233 500 000 kilómetros<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Primero, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2,5</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>160&#160;934</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>402&#160;335</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> centímetros. Luego, como <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>100&#160;000</m:mn><m:mtext> centímetros</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext> kilómetro</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math>, se obtiene <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>402&#160;335</m:mn><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>100&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4,02335</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> kilómetros, no 40 233 500 000 kilómetros.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">4,02335 kilómetros<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! La longitud en centímetros es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2,5</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>160&#160;934</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>402&#160;335</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. Como <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>100&#160;000</m:mn><m:mtext> centímetros</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext> kilómetro</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math>, entonces <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>402&#160;335</m:mn><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>100&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4,02335</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> kilómetros.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">402 335 kilómetros<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2,5</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>160&#160;934</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>402&#160;335</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> da una cantidad en centímetros, no en kilómetros. Para pasar de centímetros a kilómetros se divide por <m:math><m:mn>100&#160;000</m:mn></m:math>: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>402&#160;335</m:mn><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>100&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4,02335</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> kilómetros, no 402 335 kilómetros.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">0,402335 kilómetros<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La longitud en centímetros es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2,5</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>160&#160;934</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>402&#160;335</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. Luego, usando <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext> kilómetro</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>100&#160;000</m:mn><m:mtext> centímetros</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math>, resulta <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>402&#160;335</m:mn><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>100&#160;000</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4,02335</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> kilómetros. Por lo tanto, 0,402335 kilómetros es diez veces menor que el valor correcto.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Convertir 2,5 millas a centímetros</strong></p>
            <p>La regla indica que se multiplica la cantidad de millas por 160 934.</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2,5</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>×</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>160&#160;934</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>402&#160;335</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Entonces, el sendero mide 402 335 centímetros.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Usar la equivalencia entre kilómetros y centímetros</strong></p>
            <p>Se sabe que</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext> kilómetro</m:mtext>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>100&#160;000</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext> centímetros</m:mtext>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, para convertir de centímetros a kilómetros se divide por 100 000.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Convertir 402 335 centímetros a kilómetros</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>402&#160;335</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>÷</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>100&#160;000</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>4,02335</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>El sendero mide 4,02335 kilómetros.</p>
            <p>La alternativa correcta es la <strong>B</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>